An investigation is underway after a man’s body was found in the street on a housing estate this morning. Police were called at around 7am to reports of a man found collapsed.     A man in his 50s was pronounced dead at the scene, on the Ridge Estate in Lancaster.   His family has been informed. Lancashire Live reports that in a statement the police said: "We were called at 7am today (February 5) to Patterdale Road, Lancaster, to reports that a man had been found collapsed in the street. "Sadly, a man in his 50s was pronounced dead at the scene. His family have been informed and our thoughts are with them at this sad time.   People have been paying tribute to the man on social media. Sarah Roper said: "Rip. Such a wonderful man." Marina Belle wrote: "How very very sad...thoughts go out to family and friends xxx." Julia Duncan said: "So sad thinking of the family." Carol Jackson commented: "Thinking of the family at this very sad time." Paula Sharpe Clegg wrote: "How sad, and so young, thinking of his family." And Natalie Vranjes said: "So sad to hear this." We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. For the latest news and breaking news visit: /news Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow our social media accounts here on facebook.com/DailyExpress and @daily_express 